activity.title: ohcnetwork/care_fe#10474
activity.text:
Hello,

I'm Mohammed Imaduddin, a pre-final year computer science student from India. I'm interested in this project as the required stack (React, Node.js, TypeScript, Django) aligns well with my expertise.

To better understand the project, I researched FHIR standards and learned that they are a set of standards for exchanging healthcare data electronically, developed by HL7 to improve interoperability between healthcare systems. I found it particularly interesting that FHIR supports RESTful APIs, making it easy to work with modern web technologies.

To get hands-on experience, I set up the CARE frontend locally and explored the codebase. Additionally, I was a new contributor in the last release of care_fe, which has given me some familiarity with the project.

Iâ€™d love to contribute to this project. Please let me know the next steps and how I can get started
